untered when taking the ratios of distances in simple geometric figures suc=
h as the pentagon, pentagram, decagon and dodecahedron. It is denoted phi, =
or sometimes tau. The designations &quot;phi&quot; (for the absolute value =
of the golden ratio conjugate 1/phi) and &quot;Phi&quot; (for the larger qu=
antity phi) are sometimes also used (Knott), although this usage is not nec=
essarily...">
