 <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Phi-Prime.html">phi-primes</a>.
</p>
<p>
In an apparent blatant misunderstanding of the difference between an exact =
quantity and an approximation, the character Robert Langdon in the novel <i=
><a href=3D"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1400079179/ref=3Dnosim/e=
ricstreasuretro">The
 Da Vinci Code</a></i> incorrectly defines the golden ratio to be exactly 1=
.618 (Brown
 2003, pp.&nbsp;93-95).
</p>
<p>
The legs of a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/GoldenTriangle.html"=
