ges/equations/GoldenRatio/NumberedEquation7.svg" class=3D"numberedequation"=
 style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"215" height=
=3D"50" alt=3D" phi=3D(13)/8+sum_(n=3D0)^infty((-1)^(n+1)(2n+1)!)/((n+2)!n!=
4^(2n+3)) "></td><td align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn12" class=3D"eqnum">
(12)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
(B.&nbsp;Roselle). Another fascinating connection with the <a href=3D"https=
://mathworld.wolfram.com/FibonacciNumber.html">Fibonacci
