</div>
<p>
where <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/GoldenRati=
o/Inline47.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:=
100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"18" height=3D"21" alt=3D"F_n">
 is the <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/GoldenRa=
tio/Inline48.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-widt=
h:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"n">th
 <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/FibonacciNumber.html">Fibonacci n=
umber</a>. This gives the first few convergents
 as 1, 2, 3/2, 5/3, 8/5, 13/8, 21/13, 34/21, ... (OEIS <a href=3D"http://oe=
is.org/A000045">A000045</a>
 and <a href=3D"http://oeis.org/A000045">A000045</a>), which are good to 0,=
