" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"161" heigh=
t=3D"42" alt=3D" phi=3Dlim_(n-&gt;infty)x_n=3Dlim_(n-&gt;infty)(F_n)/(F_(n-=
1)), "></td><td align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn20" class=3D"eqnum">
(20)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
as first proved by Scottish mathematician Robert Simson in 1753 (Wells 1986=
, p.&nbsp;62; Livio 2002, p.&nbsp;101).
</p>
<p>
